{
  "doc_id": "35679",
  "text": "The contact impedance of the voltage electrode does not add to the measured voltage as the current flowing through the voltage electrodes is negligible. Only the current electrodes contribute towards the contact impedance and hence to the measured voltages. For a conventional electrode, the voltage drop in the contact impedance is included in the measured voltage [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
